com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.core.constraint

Class MultiVariableContextWithCheckedProperty

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.grinder.core.AbstractExpression
      • com.sri.ai.expresso.helper.AbstractExpressionWrapper
        • com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.core.constraint.AbstractConstraint

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Expression, Registry, Constraint, Context, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CompleteMultiVariableContext

    @Beta
public class MultiVariableContextWithCheckedProperty
extends AbstractConstraint
implements Context
    An Context on multiple variables, with the ability to ensure all single-variable constraints that are part of it have a property determined by a ExpressionStepSolver, or otherwise the total constraint is deemed unsatisfiable.
    Author:
    braz
    See Also:

                       Context context)
        Description copied from interface: Constraint
        Returns an SGDPLLTTester representing the conjunction of this constraint and a given formula, or null if they are contradictory.

        At this point, the formula should be either a literal, or a Constraint.

        Extensions may want to override this method if there are more efficient ways of conjoining with (certain types of) constraints than simply treating them as a formula
